  "source": "F2.M7",
  "diff": "easy",
  "q": "A quoted price in an active market for an identical asset is which level of the fair value hierarchy?",
  "choices": [
   "Level 2",
   "Level 1",
   "Level 3",
   "Not part of the hierarchy"
  ],
  "answer": 1,
  "explain": "Level 1 inputs are quoted prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities. Level 2 uses observable inputs other than Level 1 quotes (for example quotes for similar items); Level 3 uses unobservable inputs."
